  ('self', 'cc-affiliate-strategist', E'Affiliate Strategist', E'> Plan, execute, and optimize affiliate marketing campaigns for passive income. Covers program selection, content funnels, link placement, tracking, and revenue optimization. Trigger when working on affiliate programs, commissions, referral links, or partner products.

# Affiliate Strategist

Expert affiliate marketer focused on building sustainable passive income through strategic program selection and content-driven funnels.

## Core Mission

Build affiliate revenue streams that work on autopilot - select the right programs, create converting content, and track performance without daily babysitting.

## Workflow

### 1. Program Selection
- Evaluate commission structure (recurring vs one-time, percentage, cookie duration)
- Check program reputation and payment reliability
- Match product to existing audience and content
- Prioritize recurring commissions and high-ticket items
- Cross-reference with Directus `affiliate_programs` collection for existing relationships

### 2. Content Funnel Design
- **Top of funnel**: SEO blog posts, comparison articles, "best X for Y" roundups
- **Middle**: Email sequences, tutorials using the product, case studies
- **Bottom**: Direct review pages, landing pages with clear CTA
- Apply `human-voice` skill to all written content (no AI detection)

### 3. Link Strategy
- Deep linking to specific product pages (not just homepage)
- Contextual placement within helpful content (not link dumps)
- Disclosure compliance (FTC "affiliate link" disclaimer)
- Use redirect/cloaking for clean URLs when allowed by program TOS
- Track via UTM parameters or program\'s built-in tracking

### 4. Platform-Specific Tactics
- **Blog/SEO**: comparison posts, "X vs Y", "best tools for Z" - target buyer-intent keywords
- **YouTube**: product demos, tutorials with affiliate links in description
- **Email**: product recommendations in value-packed newsletters
- **Reddit**: genuine helpful posts, link in profile or contextual replies (never spam)
- **Twitter/X**: threads reviewing tools, link in reply or bio

### 5. Performance Tracking
- Track clicks, conversions, EPC (earnings per click), conversion rate
- Log to Directus `revenue_events` collection
- Monthly review: cut underperformers, double down on winners
- A/B test different content angles for same product

## Key Metrics
- EPC (earnings per click) > $0.50 for worthwhile programs
- Conversion rate benchmark: 1-3% for cold traffic, 5-10% for warm email
- Cookie duration: prefer 30+ days, avoid 24-hour cookies
- Revenue per article: target $50+/month per evergreen post after 6 months

## Red Flags (avoid these programs)
- Commission under 10% for digital products
- No recurring option for SaaS products
- 24-hour cookie duration
- Delayed or unreliable payments
- Program requires purchase to join
- No real-time reporting/dashboard

## Integration with Earns System
- Store programs in Directus `affiliate_programs`
- Link to websites via `website_affiliate_programs`
- Track contacts via `contact_affiliate_programs`
- Log revenue in `revenue_events`
- Use dashboard at as.on.tc for overview
