  ('self', 'cc-cover-generator', E'cover-generator', E'> Generate product covers, thumbnails, and banners for Gumroad/CodeCanyon/ Product Hunt via Playwright HTML→PNG. Use when creating marketing assets for a new product or updating existing ones. Covers size-specific design rules (readability at small sizes), brand guidelines, and pitfalls from real use.

# Generate Product Covers

Use this skill when a product needs thumbnails, covers, or banners across platforms.

## Where it lives

```
resources/cover-generator/
├── generate.mjs              # Playwright script, runs HTML → PNG
├── templates/
│   └── product-cover.html    # Main template with placeholders
│   └── product-thumb.html    # Thumbnail-specific template (text-minimal)
├── output/                   # Generated PNGs, {product}-{size}.png
├── node_modules/             # playwright (installed via npm)
└── package.json
```

## Invocation

```bash
# Generate all sizes for a product
node resources/cover-generator/generate.mjs --product <slug>

# Generate specific size only
node resources/cover-generator/generate.mjs --product <slug> --size gumroad-cover
```

## Size presets

| Size name | Dimensions | Use |
|-----------|-----------|-----|
| `gumroad-cover` | 1280×720 | Gumroad product page hero |
| `gumroad-thumb` | 600×600 | Gumroad listing thumbnail — **displayed at ~88×88px** |
| `codecanyon-preview` | 590×300 | CodeCanyon item page |
| `producthunt` | 1270×760 | Product Hunt launch |
| `og` | 1200×630 | Social share / OpenGraph |

## CRITICAL design rules — readability at actual display size

### Thumbnail (88×88 display) = title + visual marker ONLY
Gumroad and most marketplaces display "600×600" thumbnails scaled down to
~88×88 in product lists. At that size:

- **DO NOT include tagline text** — it becomes an unreadable blur
- **DO NOT include price** — same problem
- **DO NOT include long product names** — 2-3 words max, huge font
- **DO NOT include feature lists or badges with small text**
- **DO** use: brand color block, massive title, one visual icon/letter
- **DO** test by viewing the output scaled to 88×88 pixels

Example BAD (what went wrong first time):
```
CODECRATE
ImageCrate
AI Image SEO for WordPress.
Your API key. 10-50x cheaper than alternatives.
[WordPress + WooCommerce]
```
→ At 88px: only "ImageCrate" readable, rest is illegible noise.

Example GOOD:
```
┌──────────────┐
│              │
│  IC          │  ← 2-letter monogram, 60% of canvas
│              │
│  ImageCrate  │  ← single line, big font
└──────────────┘
```

### Cover (1280×720 display ~full width) = can have more text
The big Gumroad cover is shown ~1280px wide, so tagline IS readable. Rules:
- Title: 48-56px minimum
- Tagline: 20-24px minimum
- Max 2 lines of tagline
- Badge OK here
- Price tag OK here

### Product Hunt (1270×760) = same as cover but reserve bottom-right for PH logo

### OG (1200×630) = strip title + subtitle, no price (users see this on Twitter/Slack cards)

## Brand guidelines (CodeCrate)

- Font: Inter 700/800 for titles, 400 for body
- Primary bg: `linear-gradient(135deg, #0F172A, #1E293B, #0F172A)`
- Accent: `#22D3EE` (cyan)
- Highlight: `#2563EB` (blue)
- Text: white / `#94A3B8` (slate) for secondary
- Decorative: blurred gradient orbs (cyan + blue)
- Brand mark: "CODECRATE" top-left, uppercase, letter-spaced, low opacity

## Product config format

Add to the `PRODUCTS` object in `generate.mjs`:

```js
\'imagecrate\': {
  title: \'ImageCrate\',
  tagline: \'AI Image SEO for WordPress.<br>Your API key. <span class="highlight">10-50x cheaper</span> than alternatives.\',
  badge: \'WordPress + WooCommerce\',
  price: \'$29\',
  priceLabel: \'one-time\',
  // NEW: thumbnail-only content, minimal text
  thumb: {
    monogram: \'IC\',           // 2-letter short code for big thumbnail display
    shortTitle: \'ImageCrate\', // single line title for thumbnail
  },
},
```

The script uses `thumb.*` fields when generating `gumroad-thumb` (or any
other thumbnail-sized output). Falls back to main fields if thumb is missing.

## Known issues to auto-fix

### 1. Thumbnails showing unreadable taglines (discovered 2026-04-05)
**Problem**: First ImageCrate thumbnail included tagline, badge, and full
subtitle. All unreadable at 88px display.

**Fix**: Created separate `product-thumb.html` template and `thumb` config
field. Thumbnail template renders only: brand mark + monogram + short title.

**Prevention**: When adding a new product, always set `thumb.monogram` and
`thumb.shortTitle`. Never reuse the main cover layout for thumbnails.

### 2. Font loading race condition
Playwright sometimes screenshots before Google Fonts finish loading, resulting
in fallback font. Always wait 1000ms after `setContent()` before screenshotting.

### 3. Gradient orbs overflow on small sizes
On 600×600 and smaller, the 400px orb extends off canvas. Use relative sizes
(e.g., `width: 40vw`) or scale orb sizes per template.

## Debugging workflow

1. Generate → open PNG in preview
2. Scale mentally to display size (e.g., 600×600 thumb → 88×88 actual)
3. If ANY text is unreadable, redesign that template
4. Cross-platform check: does cover work on Twitter card? Product Hunt?
   Gumroad search results?

## Related skills

- `gumroad-publish` — uses output of this skill for thumbnail and cover uploads
  at `resources/cover-generator/output/<slug>-gumroad-thumb.png` and
  `<slug>-gumroad-cover.png`
