  ('self', 'cc-gumroad-publish', E'gumroad-publish', E'> Publish digital products to Gumroad via Playwright automation. Use when the user wants to create, upload, or update a Gumroad product (zip file, cover, thumbnail, description, price) programmatically. Covers login session reuse, DOM quirks (dynamic file inputs, audio/cover input collisions), multi-tab structure (Product vs Content), and safe draft mode.

# Publish to Gumroad

Use this skill when automating Gumroad product creation or updates.

## Pre-built scripts (in earns-strategy repo)

```
resources/auto-publish/
├── scripts/
│   ├── gumroad-login.mjs         # One-time interactive login (saves session)
│   ├── gumroad-upload.mjs        # Auto-upload a product (uses saved session)
│   ├── gumroad-inspect.mjs       # Dump file inputs on any page (debug)
│   ├── gumroad-inspect-modal.mjs # Inspect after clicking upload buttons
│   └── <product>.json            # Product config per product
├── .gumroad-session/             # Persistent browser state (gitignored)
└── screenshots/<slug>/           # Debug screenshots per run
```

## Invocation pattern

```bash
# One-time (interactive, user solves CAPTCHA):
node resources/auto-publish/scripts/gumroad-login.mjs

# Create new product:
node resources/auto-publish/scripts/gumroad-upload.mjs \\
  --config resources/auto-publish/scripts/<product>.json

# Edit existing product (re-upload files, fix metadata):
node resources/auto-publish/scripts/gumroad-upload.mjs \\
  --config resources/auto-publish/scripts/<product>.json \\
  --edit-url https://gumroad.com/products/<id>/edit

# Headless mode (no browser window):
... --headless
```

## Config file format

```json
{
  "slug": "imagecrate",
  "productName": "ImageCrate — AI Image SEO Optimizer for WordPress",
  "productDir": "/absolute/path/to/product",
  "zipFile": "product-v1.0.0.zip",
  "coverPath": "/absolute/path/to/cover.png",
  "thumbPath": "/absolute/path/to/thumbnail.png",
  "price": 29,
  "description": "One-paragraph description. Gets typed into the rich text editor."
}
```

Credentials come from `{productDir}/.env` with `GUMROAD_EMAIL` and `GUMROAD_PASSWORD`.

## Critical DOM gotchas (save hours of debugging)

### 1. CAPTCHA on first login — MUST use persistent session
Gumroad shows reCAPTCHA for automated logins. **Cannot bypass programmatically.**

Solution: `chromium.launchPersistentContext(sessionDir, { headless: false })`.
User solves CAPTCHA once. Browser state (cookies, localStorage) persists to disk.
All future runs reuse the session with `headless: true`.

### 2. File inputs have ambiguous positions — select by `accept` attribute
The `/products/{id}/edit` page has multiple `input[type="file"]` with no useful
`id`, `name`, or `aria-label`. Their ORDER in the DOM changes over time. DO NOT
use `fileInputs[0]`, `fileInputs[1]` — those change meaning.

**Identification strategy:**

| Input purpose | accept attribute | multiple | When it exists |
|---------------|------------------|----------|----------------|
| Description rich-text images | `.jpeg,.jpg,.png,.gif,.webp` | `true` | Always (inside contenteditable) |
| Description audio | `.mp3,.wav,.flac,.wma,.aac,.m4a` | `false` | Always |
| **Thumbnail** | `.jpeg,.jpg,.png,.gif,.webp` | `false` | Always |
| **Cover** (rich media) | `.jpeg,.jpg,.png,.gif,.mov,.m4v,.mpeg,.mpg,.mp4,.wmv` | `true` | ONLY after clicking "Upload images or videos" button |

**Key insight:** Cover input is the ONLY one that accepts **both** images AND videos.
Match with: `/mp4/.test(accept) && /png|jpg|jpeg/.test(accept)`.

### 3. Cover input is DYNAMIC — must click button first
The Cover file input does NOT exist in the DOM until you click the
**"Upload images or videos"** button under the `<h2>Cover</h2>` section.

```javascript
// WRONG — input not in DOM yet
await page.locator(\'#cover\').setInputFiles(path);

// RIGHT — click button to instantiate input, then target it
await page.click(\'button:has-text("Upload images or videos")\');
await page.waitForTimeout(1500);
const coverInput = await findCoverInput(page); // helper uses the mp4+image signature
await coverInput.setInputFiles(path);
```

### 4. Zip file lives on a DIFFERENT tab
The downloadable zip is NOT on `/products/{id}/edit` — it\'s on `/products/{id}/edit/content`.
Navigate there separately. The content tab has exactly ONE file input: `input[type="file"][name="file"]`.

### 5. Multi-step save flow
1. Fill Product tab (name, price, description, thumbnail, cover) → click "Save changes"
2. Navigate to Content tab → upload zip → click "Save changes"
3. Product is now a complete draft. User clicks "Publish and continue" manually.

### 6. Draft mode is the default AFTER save — safe by design
After "Save changes", Gumroad keeps the product as draft unless user clicks
"Publish and continue". Script should NEVER click publish — always leave it to
the human for final review.

### 7. Rich text description editor
Description uses a contenteditable div (not a textarea). Click it and use
`page.keyboard.type()` to enter text. HTML tags inside config description will
be typed literally — write plain text, not HTML.

### 8. Price field
The price input accepts dollar amounts as plain numbers (e.g. `"29"` not `"$29"`).

### 9. Product URL after creation
After creating a new product, Gumroad redirects to `/products/{id}/edit/content`
(content tab), NOT `/edit`. If you want to upload thumbnail/cover next, navigate
back to `/products/{id}/edit` first.

### 11. Thumbnail/Cover uploads are ASYNC — wait for <img> to appear before Save
File uploads on Gumroad are asynchronous. `setInputFiles()` returns immediately
but Gumroad takes 5-60 seconds to POST to their CDN. If you click "Save changes"
before the upload finishes, the thumbnail is silently dropped (empty section,
no error). **Always wait for the `<img>` element** to appear in the thumbnail
section before saving:

```javascript
await thumbInput.setInputFiles(thumbPath);
await page.waitForFunction(() => {
  const h2 = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(\'h2\'))
    .find(el => el.textContent.trim() === \'Thumbnail\');
  if (!h2) return false;
  let parent = h2.parentElement;
  for (let i = 0; i < 5 && parent; i++) {
    for (const img of parent.querySelectorAll(\'img\')) {
      if (img.src && img.complete && img.naturalWidth > 50) return true;
    }
    parent = parent.parentElement;
  }
  return false;
}, { timeout: 60000 });
```

The successful upload URL looks like `https://public-files.gumroad.com/<hash>`.

### 10. Thumbnail file input disappears after upload — must click "Remove" to replace
Once a thumbnail is set, its `<input type="file">` is removed from the DOM and
replaced with an `<img>` preview + a `[aria-label="Remove"]` button. To swap
the thumbnail:

```javascript
// Find the Remove button inside the Thumbnail <section> and click it.
await page.evaluate(() => {
  const removeBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll(\'[aria-label="Remove"]\'));
  for (const btn of removeBtns) {
    let cur = btn;
    for (let d = 0; d < 15 && cur; d++) {
      const h2 = cur.querySelector?.(\'h2\');
      if (h2 && h2.textContent.trim() === \'Thumbnail\') {
        btn.click();
        return;
      }
      cur = cur.parentElement;
    }
  }
});
await page.waitForTimeout(2000); // Wait for input to reappear
// Then find the input and setInputFiles() as usual.
```

See `gumroad-update-thumb.mjs` for a standalone script that only swaps the thumbnail.
Same pattern likely applies to Cover (untested).

## Helper functions reference

See `gumroad-upload.mjs` for working implementations:

- `findThumbnailInput(page)` — selects image-only, single-file, non-video input
- `findCoverInput(page)` — selects input whose accept contains both images AND mp4
- Inspection scripts (`gumroad-inspect.mjs`) dump all file inputs with context when
  debugging a new Gumroad layout change.

## Debugging workflow when Gumroad changes their UI

1. Run `gumroad-inspect.mjs --url <edit-url>` to dump all file inputs
2. Run `gumroad-inspect-modal.mjs` to see inputs created dynamically after clicks
3. Every step in `gumroad-upload.mjs` takes a screenshot — check `screenshots/<slug>/`
   to see exactly where it went wrong
4. When a selector breaks, update it via the `accept` attribute signature rather
   than DOM position

## Related skills

- `cover-generator` workflow: `resources/cover-generator/` uses Playwright to
  generate PNG covers from HTML templates. Gumroad upload expects these outputs at
  `resources/cover-generator/output/<slug>-gumroad-cover.png` and `-gumroad-thumb.png`.

## What this skill does NOT handle yet

- Publishing (clicking "Publish and continue") — intentionally left manual
- Custom pricing tiers / pay-what-you-want
- Product variants / versions
- Category selection
- SEO / URL customization
- Tag management
- Gumroad API (this uses browser automation because Gumroad\'s public API doesn\'t
  expose product creation)
