  ('self', 'cc-human-voice', E'human-voice', E'> Write content that passes AI detection and reads as human-written. Apply when writing blog posts, product descriptions, emails, social posts, or any public-facing copy. Trigger automatically whenever producing written content intended for publication.

# Human Voice Writing

Apply these rules to any content meant to sound human-written.

## Punctuation

- Use `-` (hyphen/dash), never `—` (em dash) or `–` (en dash)
- Avoid ellipsis `...` used for dramatic effect
- Use contractions: "don\'t", "it\'s", "you\'ll" — not "do not", "it is", "you will"

## Banned words (replace immediately)

| Banned | Use instead |
|---|---|
| delve | explore, look at, dig into |
| leverage | use, apply, take advantage of |
| utilize | use |
| crucial / vital | important, key |
| comprehensive | complete, full, thorough |
| robust | strong, solid, reliable |
| streamline | simplify, speed up |
| moreover / furthermore | also, and, on top of that |
| in conclusion | (just end the paragraph) |
| it\'s worth noting | (just say it directly) |
| it\'s important to note | (just say it directly) |
| certainly / absolutely | (remove entirely) |
| of course | (remove entirely) |
| I would be happy to | (remove entirely) |
| as an AI | (never say this) |
| in today\'s world | (remove entirely) |
| in the realm of | (remove entirely) |
| game-changer | (avoid) |
| cutting-edge | new, modern, latest |
| state-of-the-art | (avoid) |
| seamless | smooth, easy |
| ecosystem | (avoid unless technical context) |

## Sentence patterns to avoid

- Starting every bullet point with a verb (sounds like AI instructions)
- 3-part lists for everything ("fast, reliable, and secure")
- Perfectly parallel structure across all sentences
- Hedging every claim ("this may help", "could potentially", "might be")
- Ending sections with a summary of what was just said
- Asking rhetorical questions then immediately answering them

## What makes writing sound human

- Vary sentence length - short punchy ones mixed with longer ones
- Occasional sentence fragments. Like this.
- Opinions stated directly without hedging
- Specific numbers and details over vague claims
- Imperfect transitions ("Anyway,", "Here\'s the thing -", "So,")
- Start sentences with "And" or "But" occasionally
- Asymmetric lists (not always 3 items)

## AI detection red flags (never do these)

- Numbered intro + bullet body + summary conclusion structure
- Starting response with "Certainly! Here\'s..." or "Great question!"
- Using "I" excessively when writing third-person content
- Every paragraph exactly 3-4 sentences
- Zero typos + perfect grammar throughout (too clean)
